## How You Can Help

### 1. Adopt
Give one of these dogs a forever home. The adoption process is easier than you think, and you'll gain a loyal companion for life.

### 2. Foster
Can't commit long-term? Foster provides temporary care while we find permanent homes. Even a few weeks can save a life!

### 3. Share
Spread the word on social media. Tag friends who might be interested. A single share could be the connection that saves a life.

### 4. Donate
Help cover transport costs to move dogs to safety, medical care, and basic supplies. Every dollar helps.

### 5. Contact a Rescue
Many rescue organizations pull dogs from high-risk shelters. If you know a rescue, please forward this list!

---

## Why This Matters

Every year, millions of dogs enter shelters across the United States. Many are wonderful, loving companions who simply found themselves without a home through no fault of their own.

At kill shelters, space is limited and time runs out quickly. Dogs on euthanasia lists may have only days - or hours - left.

**But you can change that.**

One person sharing this post could reach the exact person who's been looking for their new best friend. One foster home could buy precious time. One adoption could save two lives - the dog you take home, and the one who gets their shelter spot.

